## Limitations

The findings are based on available data and studies, which may not cover all bird species or regions equally. The rapid pace of climate change and its complex interactions with other environmental factors make it challenging to predict long-term impacts accurately. Additionally, the adaptability of bird species varies, and some may not have been studied extensively, leading to gaps in understanding their responses to climate change.

